  "texts": [
    "F is a lattice-complete principal possibility frame; 2.",
    "P is the set of all principal downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ plus ∅, ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice, and R i satisfies R-rule and R⇒win.Proof.",
    "The implication from part 1 to part 2 follows from Definitions 4.36 and 4.46 and Fact 4.42.From part 2 to part 1, given the characterization of principal frames in terms of i being a total operation in Fact 4.41, it suffices to show that if R i satisfies R-rule and R⇒win, then i is such a total operation, which is to say that for anyy ∈ S ⊥, if {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y} is nonempty (where ↓y = {y ′ ∈ S ⊥ | y ′ ⊑ ⊥ y}) then it has a maximum in ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩.",
    "Since F is lattice-complete, this is equivalent to the claim that {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y} ∈ {x ∈ S ⊥ | R i ⊥ (x) ⊆ ↓y}.",
    "(4.1) Recall from the definition of R i ⊥ in Definition 4.23 that R i ⊥ (⊥) = {⊥} and for x ∈ S, R i ⊥ (x) = R i (x) ∪ {⊥}."
